This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. The paper also proposes a novel optimization algorithm for the Average-Precision loss, which is a commonly used metric in object detection evaluation. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as deep learning and perceptron learning, which are covered in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The optimization algorithm proposed in the paper involves backpropagation, which is a common technique in Neural Networks (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on various benchmarks, which is related to Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
